            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I access my storage unit anytime?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Fort Knox Self Storage provides 24/7 access with a personal access code. No restricted hours — ideal for oil field workers and contractors on irregular schedules in the Uintah Basin."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Do you offer RV and boat storage in Vernal?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Fort Knox Self Storage offers outdoor parking spaces for cars, trucks, RVs, boats, campers, and motorhomes. Call James at 435-828-7710 for current availability and pricing."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What size storage unit do I need?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "A 20-foot container holds the contents of a typical apartment. A 40-foot container holds a full home and garage. Call James at 435-828-7710 for a personalized recommendation."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Is there storage available today in Vernal?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Fort Knox Self Storage typically has immediate availability. Call James at 435-828-7710 to check current availability and move in the same day."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Can I use storage for oil field equipment or contractor supplies?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Yes. Many Fort Knox customers use 40-foot containers for tools, equipment, and business inventory. The 24/7 access and steel construction make it ideal for oil field workers and contractors in the Uintah Basin."
